{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-14615/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-14615"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["1:46:15"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["medium shot"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["low"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["mobile, handheld, pan, tracking"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["single shot"]}}],"summary":{"none":["A yellow balloon falls onto a man."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-14615/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-14615","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-14615/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-14615"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-14615/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-14615/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-14615/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-14615/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-14615/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-14615/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-14615/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-14615/canvas/1/a3c1b13a-7d07-479b-b300-f9d20d40bc07","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-07-02T19:59:02.296Z","creator":"Ada ","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>The New Year’s Eve party hosted by the Chelsea Art Club was a notorious celebration. Held at the Royal Albert Hall from 1910 to 1959 (with a short suspension during World War II), the riotous party featured themed costumes, floats, dancing, performers, and ample libations. The stroke of midnight was marked with the dropping of thousands of balloons and the destruction of the floats, a tradition reflected in this scene (LIFE, “Life Goes to the Chelsea Arts Ball”). Though the wild festivities were banned from the Royal Albert Hall in 1959 after a reveler set off a smoke bomb on the dance floor, the party continues to happen annually to this day at the Chelsea Arts Club’s premises with one crucial difference—no cameras allowed (Sampson, “<a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW14554431 BCX4\" href=\"https://www.tatler.com/gallery/chelsea-arts-club-ball-greatest-new-years-eve-fancy-dress-party\"><u>Was the scandalous Chelsea Arts Ball</u></a>”).&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-14615/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:23.961484872611294,36.86703821656046,319.7248208598726,200.16222133757958"}}}]}]}]}